{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/570", "id": 871969406, "node_id": "PR_kwDOD6Q_ss4z-TJ-", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot5/pull/570", "diff_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot5/pull/570.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot5/pull/570.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/issues/570", "number": 570, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "fBits is 4 bytes", "user": {"login": "jpivarski", "id": 1852447, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4NTI0NDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1852447?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski", "html_url": "https://github.com/jpivarski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "This PR _reverses_ the second \"fix\" in #454, which was motivated by issue #438, raised by @kratsg.\r\n\r\nReading the text of PR #454, it's clear that I didn't believe `fBits` is actually 1 byte, I did it as an expedient because the file from Delphes had sometimes 4 bytes, sometimes 6 bytes, and at least assuming it's 1 byte would prevent it from raising error messages in `AsGrouped`. Reverting that may break @kratsg's workflow, but it didn't actually need the `fBits`\u2014they were just coming along for the ride in `AsGrouped`. Would it be possible to instead avoid `AsGrouped`?\r\n\r\nThe file that this PR is based on, from @tfruth, demonstrates that the `fBits` really is 4 bytes. Maybe the Delphes ROOT writer is just wrong here. Anyway, the code can only be one way (PR #454 shows that I tried and failed to find any indicator for \"4 bytes\" vs \"6 bytes\") and this appears to be the correct one.\r\n\r\nBoth of you are affected by this. If it matters, please test against this PR!", "created_at": "2022-03-04T19:53:58Z", "updated_at": "2022-03-09T00:13:37Z", "closed_at": "2022-03-07T17:38:29Z", "merged_at": "2022-03-07T17:38:28Z", "merge_commit_sha": "ccae426ae94dfaeed15b625d80d42c8c586a5082", "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/570/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/570/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/issues/570/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/statuses/839544a6220a71340b1cbf012fc004f1b6a7d973", "head": {"label": "scikit-hep:jpivarski/fBits-is-4-bytes", "ref": "jpivarski/fBits-is-4-bytes", "sha": "839544a6220a71340b1cbf012fc004f1b6a7d973", "user": {"login": "scikit-hep", "id": 23454624, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjIzNDU0NjI0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23454624?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/starred{/owne